olive oil
2 potato
3 clove garlic
½ lemon
1 cucumber
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
½ sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 sachet Tuscan Herb Seasoning

• Boil the kettle. Cut potato into large chunks.
Finely chop garlic. Slice lemon into wedges.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water
and a pinch of salt. Cook potato in the boiling
water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a
fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain potato and set aside.
• Return saucepan to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook 1/2 the garlic, stirring,
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a
generous pinch of salt. Stir to combine, then
remove from heat.
• Return potato to the pan and toss to coat. Lightly
crush with a fork. Season to taste and cover to
keep warm.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the potato looks dry!

• While the potato is cooking, roughly chop
cucumber.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, fine
breadcrumbs, the egg, Tuscan herb seasoning,
vegetable stock powder (see ingredients), the
remaining garlic and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of
beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per
person). Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of
olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and
cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches
if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add onion chutney
and a splash of water and gently toss to coat.

• Meanwhile, combine cucumber, mixed salad
leaves, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of
olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the salad.

• Divide Tuscan beef meatballs and onion glaze,
lemon crushed potatoes and cucumber salad
between plates.
• Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!